WEBVTT

00:40.319 --> 00:55.319
<font color="#ffff80"><b>Fixed & Synced by bozxphd.Enjoy The Flick</b></font>

01:03.320 --> 01:04.321
(GLASS SPEAKING PAWNEE)

01:04.440 --> 01:07.330
<i>It's okay, son...</i>

01:08.600 --> 01:13.481
<i>I know you want this to be over.</i>

01:20.000 --> 01:22.128
<i>I'm right here.</i>

01:26.520 --> 01:29.171
<i>I will be right here...</i>

01:36.680 --> 01:39.081
<i>But, you don't give up.</i>

01:42.080 --> 01:45.050
<i>You hear me?</i>

01:46.840 --> 01:51.926
<i>As long as you can still
grab a breath, you fight.</i>

01:53.520 --> 01:56.967
<i>You breathe... keep breathing.</i>

03:42.400 --> 03:43.447
(GLASS CLICKS TONGUE)

03:43.520 --> 03:44.851
GLASS: Hawk.

04:09.840 --> 04:11.604
(GUNS COCKING)
(GLASS CLICKS TONGUE)

04:11.720 --> 04:13.210
(GLASS SPEAKING PAWNEE)

04:31.080 --> 04:33.082
Ah, shit.

04:34.920 --> 04:37.571
Goddamn sumbitches.

04:39.720 --> 04:42.405
The sumbitch
got shit for brains.

04:42.520 --> 04:44.045
(GRUMBLING)

04:47.920 --> 04:48.921
You seen Coulter?

04:49.080 --> 04:50.081
TRAPPER: Nope.

04:53.040 --> 04:54.371
Listen up!

04:54.600 --> 04:56.045
When them plews is cleaned,

04:56.120 --> 04:58.248
I want you to hoop 'em up
real tight.

04:58.600 --> 05:02.559
Remember, we're not doing
no 15-pelt bales!

05:02.560 --> 05:03.560
We're going
30-pelt bales!

05:03.600 --> 05:04.601
HENRY: Fitzgerald!

05:05.560 --> 05:06.641
Cap'n.

05:06.720 --> 05:09.644
Where are we with the haul?
What are you thinking?

05:10.920 --> 05:13.844
I'm thinking, whatever it is
they're hunting out there...

05:13.920 --> 05:15.843
I hope it don't need
another shot.

05:15.960 --> 05:18.088
Make sure we're ready
to head out by dawn.

05:18.160 --> 05:19.207
Been done by this morning.

05:19.280 --> 05:20.725
I'd have liked
to be out by how,

05:20.840 --> 05:22.888
but the men
are too tired.

05:22.960 --> 05:24.360
We're only a few days
from the fort.

05:24.400 --> 05:25.447
We're trapped out.

05:25.520 --> 05:28.922
All we have to worry about
is fresh meat for the boys.

05:29.240 --> 05:31.846
Well, you, uh, seen Coulter?

05:31.920 --> 05:33.604
(JIM PANTING)

05:34.640 --> 05:37.644
JIM: Hey, we took down
an elk. A big one.

05:38.640 --> 05:40.449
We need help
to haul the meat back.

05:40.600 --> 05:42.045
Let me know
when it's on the spit.

05:42.120 --> 05:43.406
I'll help you
with it then.

05:43.480 --> 05:45.244
Come on, I need your help.

05:45.320 --> 05:47.641
We needed help when we were
loading them bales.

05:47.960 --> 05:50.645
I been eating this damn
beaver meat so long...

05:50.960 --> 05:52.928
I'm starting to
miss my wife's cooking.

05:53.280 --> 05:54.691
I'm starting
to miss your wife.

05:54.760 --> 05:55.807
Shut up.

05:56.160 --> 05:57.321
COULTER: Help!

05:58.160 --> 05:59.491
Help.

06:00.000 --> 06:01.331
TRAPPER 1: Is that Coulter?
(MEN CLAMORING)

06:01.640 --> 06:03.802
You go get the Captain.

06:03.960 --> 06:05.291
STUBBY BILL: Jesus Christ.

06:08.440 --> 06:10.169
TRAPPER 2: Anybody see them?

06:10.480 --> 06:11.811
TRAPPER 3: Stay quiet.

06:11.960 --> 06:13.166
TRAPPER 4: Watch the ridge.

06:13.280 --> 06:14.964
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

06:15.960 --> 06:16.961
(GROANS)

06:22.640 --> 06:23.971
(HAWK SPEAKING PAWNEE)

06:24.080 --> 06:26.208
What was that?

06:32.120 --> 06:33.120
Pa?

06:33.360 --> 06:34.600
Let's go.

06:45.520 --> 06:47.045
(MEN CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

06:48.640 --> 06:49.971
(MAN SHUSHING)

06:50.040 --> 06:51.849
(HORSES WHINNYING)
(ARIKARA WARRIORS WHOOPING)

06:56.040 --> 06:57.724
They got Thomas.

07:20.880 --> 07:23.565
I can't see 'em.
I can't see 'em.

07:28.560 --> 07:30.085
HENRY: Get down!

07:31.560 --> 07:34.086
We're surrounded!
They're everywhere!

07:34.360 --> 07:36.089
HENRY: Stay here! Stay here!

07:36.200 --> 07:37.200
(PAUL GROANING)

07:37.240 --> 07:38.605
Paul, no!

07:38.880 --> 07:40.405
(PAUL SCREAMING)

07:47.400 --> 07:49.402
They want us out in the open.

07:50.280 --> 07:52.760
Nobody move!
Stay where you are!

07:53.080 --> 07:54.809
They want the pelts.

07:54.880 --> 07:56.564
We got to get
on that boat right now

07:56.640 --> 07:58.130
or we'll lose it all.

08:03.400 --> 08:05.243
(ARIKARA WARRIORS WHOOPING)

08:07.560 --> 08:09.244
(SHOUTING IN PAWNEE)

08:15.800 --> 08:19.282
Get to the boat!
To the boat, son! Move!

08:19.920 --> 08:21.251
Move, move!

08:21.680 --> 08:23.091
(BOTH GRUNTING)

08:24.280 --> 08:28.126
Leave the furs!
Leave the furs! To the boat!

08:28.760 --> 08:29.921
(YELLING)

08:31.320 --> 08:32.765
(BOTH GRUNTING)

08:47.040 --> 08:48.451
(ARIKARA WARRIOR 1 GROANING)

08:53.280 --> 08:55.442
Hawk!

09:01.440 --> 09:02.965
Hawk!

09:03.320 --> 09:04.970
Hawk!

09:15.040 --> 09:16.724
(ARIKARA WARRIOR 2 WHOOPING)

09:20.320 --> 09:21.651
(SHOUTING IN ARIKARA)

09:24.080 --> 09:25.411
(GROANING)

09:33.200 --> 09:36.522
Grab some pelts!
Come on, grab the pelts!

09:41.240 --> 09:42.924
(BOTH GRUNTING)

09:55.880 --> 09:59.566
Grab the pelts!
Grab the pelts!

10:15.680 --> 10:17.409
DAVE: Give this
to my little girl.

10:17.760 --> 10:19.762
You're coming with us.
I'll get help.

10:26.920 --> 10:29.605
GLASS: Leave the furs!
Leave the pelts!

10:30.440 --> 10:31.566
Willman!

10:32.600 --> 10:33.840
Lean on me.
Just keep going.

10:33.920 --> 10:35.081
(GROANS)

10:38.600 --> 10:40.602
Get to the boat!

10:44.080 --> 10:45.923
(ARIKARA WARRIORS WHOOPING)

10:48.000 --> 10:49.411
(YELLING)

11:02.560 --> 11:04.085
Fucking savage!

11:05.400 --> 11:07.641
Get on the fucking boat!

11:14.640 --> 11:15.926
(GROANING)

11:17.280 --> 11:18.611
Help!

11:30.640 --> 11:33.007
HENRY: Cut the rope!
Cut the rope!

11:33.320 --> 11:34.810
Wait for Amos!

11:35.000 --> 11:36.490
No! We go now!

11:36.840 --> 11:38.649
Fire the cannon!

11:49.000 --> 11:51.526
AMOS: Don't leave! Wait!

12:01.480 --> 12:03.369
(ARIKARA ELDER CHANTING)

12:37.360 --> 12:39.761
My daughter, Powaqa, is not here.

12:40.640 --> 12:42.449
Collect all the pelts we can carry.

12:43.160 --> 12:50.169
We'll trade pelts with the French
for horses and keep searching for her.

12:53.080 --> 12:54.889
HENRY:
and dust becomes flour...

12:55.520 --> 12:57.204
and when the morning
is clear...

12:57.360 --> 13:01.570
this child of God will meet
Jesus Christ himself. Amen.

13:09.600 --> 13:11.443
(MURPHY BREATHING SHAKILY)

13:16.600 --> 13:17.761
HENRY: You ready?

13:19.760 --> 13:21.091
Hold still.

13:21.320 --> 13:22.924
(MURPHY SCREAMING)

13:26.440 --> 13:27.930
ANDERSON:
Where did you learn that?

13:28.720 --> 13:31.121
My father was a doctor.
Bridger!

13:31.440 --> 13:32.680
FITZGERALD: Captain,
we got a swarm of

13:32.760 --> 13:35.604
tree niggers out here
waiting to finish the job.

13:38.960 --> 13:41.406
Tell me you got
some kind of plan.

13:46.440 --> 13:47.601
Glass?

13:48.800 --> 13:50.802
Missouri's no good.

13:51.280 --> 13:53.601
Not while the Ree's
running it.

13:53.960 --> 13:55.610
We got to
get off this boat.

13:55.800 --> 13:57.802
Oh, you want to
get off the boat?

13:59.240 --> 14:01.129
Then what do we do, huh?

14:01.480 --> 14:03.767
Take our furs and sit
out there amongst the Ree

14:03.840 --> 14:05.490
like a bunch of ducks?

14:05.800 --> 14:08.963
Only safe thing to do is track
a new course back up on land.

14:09.160 --> 14:10.491
That'll add weeks
to the trip.

14:10.680 --> 14:12.682
Better than floating
where they can get eyes on us.

14:12.960 --> 14:15.327
They got eyes on you
right now, son.

14:16.640 --> 14:19.484
What I'm saying is
we stay on the boat.

14:19.800 --> 14:22.007
Chart a course
toward the fort

14:22.120 --> 14:23.485
and take our chances
on the water.

14:23.560 --> 14:26.530
Glass knows
this territory best.

14:26.600 --> 14:28.170
It's his job
to get us home safe.

14:28.320 --> 14:29.401
Get us home safe?
Yeah.

14:29.480 --> 14:31.926
FITZGERALD: Need I remind you
we already lost 32 men?

14:32.000 --> 14:34.207
It's 33 now.
They were my men, Fitzgerald.

14:34.280 --> 14:36.123
I know how many I lost.

14:37.000 --> 14:39.651
We do like Glass says.
That's the end of it.

14:53.240 --> 14:54.571
GLASS: We have to
set the boat loose.

14:54.640 --> 14:57.166
If the Ree are tracking us,
they'll find it downriver.

14:57.480 --> 14:59.323
Best course is to
hike inland to the Grand

14:59.400 --> 15:01.084
and follow it
to Fort Kiowa.

15:01.160 --> 15:03.049
ANDERSON: On foot?

15:03.120 --> 15:04.326
It'll be winter
before we get there.

15:04.400 --> 15:06.050
Yeah, unless
we come across a post,

15:06.120 --> 15:07.246
trade for some horses.

15:07.320 --> 15:09.163
Ain't no posts
that far over!

15:09.480 --> 15:12.563
Captain, losing this boat
is a goddamn mistake.

15:12.920 --> 15:15.002
The Ree
ain't that stupid.

15:15.120 --> 15:17.600
We keep it, we can lay it up
around Arrow's Peak.

15:17.680 --> 15:19.762
Quit acting like you know
what you're talking about.

15:19.840 --> 15:21.330
Ain't nobody talking to you.

15:21.600 --> 15:23.011
Who'd listen
to you anyway?

15:23.120 --> 15:26.442
Can't find your way out of
your breeches to take a shit.

15:26.520 --> 15:29.842
All I'm saying is
Camp Rhulen is just up the way.

15:30.160 --> 15:31.924
We can hole up there.

15:32.360 --> 15:33.850
We walk.

15:34.520 --> 15:36.522
Yeah, I'm sure we will.

15:37.560 --> 15:39.324
Wish my dad
was a doctor.

15:39.400 --> 15:41.846
Then he could've bought me
a captain's job.

15:41.960 --> 15:43.291
What do we do, eh?

15:43.360 --> 15:46.523
Pray these pelts ain't rotten
if we ever get back here?

15:46.880 --> 15:48.291
HENRY: Make sure
to mark this place.

15:48.360 --> 15:50.886
We're leaving a fortune
under these rocks.

15:53.040 --> 15:54.451
Glass, chart a course.

15:54.520 --> 15:56.966
Tightest you can that
gets us around the Ree.

15:58.720 --> 16:00.370
FITZGERALD: This ain't right.

16:01.480 --> 16:04.404
We all know these furs

16:04.480 --> 16:06.482
ain't gonna be here
by the time we come back.

16:06.560 --> 16:10.121
There's no way we can haul
them all the way to the fort.

16:10.200 --> 16:12.123
Arikara are
all through the territory.

16:12.240 --> 16:13.480
We'll want
our hands free.

16:13.560 --> 16:15.483
We're gonna
lose those pelts.

16:15.560 --> 16:17.085
You rather keep the pelts
or your life?

16:17.200 --> 16:18.406
Life?

16:18.640 --> 16:21.405
What life you talking about?
I ain't got no life.

16:21.640 --> 16:23.449
I just got living
and the only way I get that

16:23.520 --> 16:25.329
is through these pelts.

16:26.720 --> 16:28.006
Fuck!

16:30.240 --> 16:33.323
Ain't no way I'm going home
after six months

16:33.400 --> 16:35.243
working my ass off
like a mule...

16:35.680 --> 16:39.002
risking my neck,
men dying, and for what?

16:39.080 --> 16:40.605
Damn near lost everything.

16:40.680 --> 16:42.921
Job's been fucked
from the start!

16:43.920 --> 16:45.922
There's the one
been fucking us.

16:46.440 --> 16:49.603
You wonder how the Ree
got the dead drop on us...

16:49.840 --> 16:51.000
when Mr. Glass
was supposed

16:51.040 --> 16:52.963
to look out
for that very thing?

16:53.280 --> 16:55.362
All them Pawnee buddies of his.

16:55.440 --> 16:58.284
Pawnee's as much against
the Ree as the rest of us.

16:58.360 --> 16:59.441
Yeah?

16:59.920 --> 17:03.606
Well, what about
his little half-breed son?

17:04.119 --> 17:06.441
What kind of savage
you think his mama was?

17:06.520 --> 17:08.363
Oh, lay off the boy, Fitz.

17:09.040 --> 17:10.804
All I'm saying is...

17:11.119 --> 17:13.805
a savage... is savage.

17:21.560 --> 17:23.210
Hey, Glass...

17:24.480 --> 17:25.720
is it true
what they say

17:25.800 --> 17:27.211
about you shooting a lieutenant

17:27.280 --> 17:29.487
while living
with them savages?

17:33.120 --> 17:36.044
Twenty-one dead soldiers
and 40 dead feathernecks.

17:36.120 --> 17:38.327
But you and your boy
the only ones to walk out alive.

17:38.440 --> 17:40.522
Kind of a miracle.

17:40.600 --> 17:41.965
HENRY: Shut up, Fitzgerald.

17:43.880 --> 17:45.166
FITZGERALD:
Is that what you did?

17:45.240 --> 17:47.641
Shot one of your own
to save this little dog here?

17:48.000 --> 17:49.286
Shut up!

17:49.480 --> 17:52.723
Why? Was he playing with
this little boy's mama, huh?

17:52.840 --> 17:54.490
Did he kill her?

17:55.160 --> 17:56.571
Hey, you can quit
polishing that rifle

17:56.640 --> 17:58.165
when I'm talking to you.

17:58.480 --> 17:59.925
I'm working on it.

18:00.000 --> 18:02.480
You can work on it
when I'm done talking to you.

18:02.840 --> 18:03.921
Look at me.

18:04.000 --> 18:05.331
HENRY: That's enough!

18:06.520 --> 18:08.761
You're forgetting
your place, boy.

18:10.080 --> 18:12.082
As far as I can tell,
my place is here

18:12.160 --> 18:14.447
on the smart end
of this rifle.

18:14.520 --> 18:16.682
HENRY:
You move along, Fitzgerald.

18:18.360 --> 18:19.771
That's an order!

18:19.840 --> 18:20.887
Listen!

18:20.960 --> 18:22.769
There's only a couple hours
of light left.

18:22.840 --> 18:25.047
We got to stash these pelts
and get rid of the boat.

18:25.120 --> 18:26.360
Let's go!
(ALL AGREEING)

18:27.480 --> 18:28.527
(SPEAKING PAWNEE)

18:28.760 --> 18:30.999
I told you to be invisible, son.

18:31.000 --> 18:32.319
At least he...

18:32.320 --> 18:36.319
If you want to survive,
keep your mouth shut.

18:36.320 --> 18:40.559
- At least he heard me...
- They don't hear your voice!

18:40.560 --> 18:43.039
They just see the color of your face.

18:43.040 --> 18:45.719
You understand?

18:45.720 --> 18:46.846
Yes.

18:51.640 --> 18:54.079
You have to listen to me, son.

18:54.080 --> 18:56.447
You have to listen.

19:01.480 --> 19:02.686
(GLASS GRUNTS)

19:08.480 --> 19:10.005
HENRY: Beckett!

19:11.160 --> 19:12.161
Weston!

19:12.320 --> 19:14.243
JONES: Why are
they not jumping?

19:14.920 --> 19:17.241
STUBBY BILL: It looks
like they changed their minds.

19:23.240 --> 19:25.242
FITZGERALD: Smart sumbitches.

19:25.920 --> 19:27.251
Smart.

19:28.200 --> 19:29.611
(GRUNTS)

19:33.600 --> 19:35.921
I ought to be
on that boat.

19:39.440 --> 19:41.442
They did the right thing.

19:46.320 --> 19:47.890
(MEN LAUGHING)

19:57.040 --> 19:58.121
(BOTH SPEAKING PAWNEE)

19:58.280 --> 19:59.770
It's time to move.

20:00.440 --> 20:01.965
Get up.

20:03.000 --> 20:04.126
We're headed out.

20:06.960 --> 20:08.564
I'm coming.

20:11.360 --> 20:13.442
It's better you lay down.

20:15.320 --> 20:19.519
When the rest of the men are ready
you send them to me.

20:19.520 --> 20:21.488
I'm going west.

20:35.920 --> 20:41.802
You are my son.

20:49.960 --> 20:51.405
(WARRIOR 1 SPEAKING ARIKARA)

20:51.720 --> 20:53.085
There are only two here.

20:53.160 --> 20:54.241
(ELK DOG SPEAKING ARIKARA)

20:54.320 --> 20:57.164
Powaqa is not here.

20:57.240 --> 20:58.366
(WARRIOR 1 SPEAKING ARIKARA)

20:58.600 --> 21:01.039
The others probably took her.

21:01.040 --> 21:02.883
They went north.

21:03.000 --> 21:04.206
(ELK DOG SPEAKING ARIKARA)

21:04.520 --> 21:08.366
We'll pick up their tracks on the mountain.

21:10.840 --> 21:12.444
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

21:16.480 --> 21:18.050
HENRY: Was it
the right decision?

21:18.160 --> 21:19.491
Leaving the boat?

21:20.480 --> 21:24.007
The Ree own that river.
They would've flanked us.

21:24.640 --> 21:27.041
We stay east of the Grand
through the mountains,

21:27.120 --> 21:28.770
we cut a week off our trip.

21:28.840 --> 21:31.889
Lands are bone dry up there.
Nothing for the Ree to hunt.

21:32.880 --> 21:34.325
HENRY: Except us.

21:34.680 --> 21:36.205
GLASS: Except us.

21:43.000 --> 21:45.002
Is it true
what Fitzgerald said?

21:46.520 --> 21:49.205
Is that why you came out
here to the edge of the world?

21:52.000 --> 21:53.161
Glass?

21:53.240 --> 21:55.083
I do like the quiet.

21:57.200 --> 21:58.531
Your boy...

21:58.840 --> 22:00.524
he's seen a lot.

22:01.200 --> 22:04.044
He got a mother
you need to get him back to?

22:08.800 --> 22:10.086
(FITZGERALD BREATHING HEAVILY)

22:10.160 --> 22:11.605
(CUTTING HAIR)

23:34.840 --> 23:36.080
(RUSTLING)

23:46.920 --> 23:48.160
(COCKS GUN)

23:59.120 --> 24:00.610
(BEAR BELLOWING)

24:15.720 --> 24:17.370
(BEAR SNORTING)

24:20.960 --> 24:22.041
(GLASS YELLS)

24:22.360 --> 24:24.203
(GROANING)

24:42.880 --> 24:44.245
(SCREAMING)

25:07.040 --> 25:08.929
(BELLOWING)

25:16.680 --> 25:18.205
(GROANING)

25:39.960 --> 25:41.803
(GLASS PANTING)

25:50.600 --> 25:52.250
(STRAINING)

26:11.160 --> 26:12.844
(FLIES BUZZING)

26:13.320 --> 26:14.481
(GRUNTS)

26:34.800 --> 26:36.848
(PANTING)

27:06.360 --> 27:07.850
(GRUNTING)

27:08.720 --> 27:10.802
(CHOKING)

27:15.040 --> 27:16.724
(SCREAMING)

28:30.120 --> 28:31.610
(BELLOWS)

28:32.560 --> 28:34.210
(GRUNTING)

28:49.880 --> 28:51.325
(CUB BELLOWING)

29:02.480 --> 29:03.561
(HAWK YELLING)

29:03.640 --> 29:05.768
JIM: Mr. Glass!

29:06.320 --> 29:07.924
There are cubs here!

29:11.520 --> 29:13.170
We got cubs here!

29:17.120 --> 29:18.804
Christ Almighty.

29:23.120 --> 29:24.645
He's down here!

29:26.760 --> 29:28.489
ANDERSON: Keep your eyes open.
There's bears around.

29:28.640 --> 29:30.529
JIM: I need your help now!

29:33.840 --> 29:35.285
HENRY: Oh, my God.

29:35.680 --> 29:37.045
(GLASS WHEEZING)

29:38.360 --> 29:40.249
Get me rags now!

29:40.320 --> 29:43.005
Give me rags
before he bleeds out. Rags.

29:43.840 --> 29:46.844
Prepare the kit. Bridger!
You hold that.

29:47.040 --> 29:48.451
(GRUNTING)

29:48.520 --> 29:50.284
Easy. Oh, my God.

29:50.360 --> 29:51.646
ANDERSON: Got to give him
credit for taking that grizz

29:51.720 --> 29:52.960
down with him.

29:53.040 --> 29:54.280
He shouldn't have shot.

29:54.360 --> 29:56.362
The place is crawling
with tree niggers.

29:56.480 --> 29:58.801
HENRY: That's enough!
That's enough!

29:58.880 --> 30:00.803
We're still
in Ree territory.

30:00.880 --> 30:02.644
He's one of our own men.

30:02.720 --> 30:04.404
(CONTINUES WHEEZING)

30:04.520 --> 30:06.807
Scout a circle around us.
North and west.

30:06.880 --> 30:08.609
Take those two with you.

30:08.680 --> 30:10.489
Bill, Fryman,
you take south and east.

30:10.560 --> 30:13.086
Watch for anyone
that might've heard that shot.

30:13.520 --> 30:15.249
We have to stitch him up.

30:15.400 --> 30:18.324
What about me? Captain?

30:18.400 --> 30:19.890
You just stay here.

30:20.320 --> 30:21.321
Hold it down.

30:21.720 --> 30:22.767
JIM: I'm so sorry, Mr. Glass.

30:22.880 --> 30:25.486
HENRY: Bridger,
press down here.

30:26.480 --> 30:28.084
JIM: He's bleeding
down here, too.

30:28.200 --> 30:29.406
(GLASS SCREAMING)

30:29.520 --> 30:31.807
ANDERSON:
They're torturing the bastard.

30:31.880 --> 30:33.723
The proper thing to do
would be...

30:34.040 --> 30:35.929
to finish him off quick.

30:36.360 --> 30:38.931
Unless he has a chance
of pulling through.

30:39.440 --> 30:40.726
(SCOFFS)

30:40.880 --> 30:42.564
Pulling through?

30:42.880 --> 30:44.882
You saw what that
grizz did to him.

30:45.000 --> 30:47.048
He'll be dead inside an hour.
Mmm-hmm.

30:48.400 --> 30:51.927
Yeah, we all will be
if he don't quit wailing like that.

30:54.680 --> 30:58.002
Toward you and twist it
into place. I'll hold him. Go.

30:58.080 --> 30:59.844
Pa.
HENRY: Hold him. Go.

31:01.080 --> 31:02.127
Go!

31:02.560 --> 31:03.686
Now!

31:08.760 --> 31:10.410
He passed out.

31:11.240 --> 31:13.925
I'll take advantage
and stitch up his neck.

31:15.080 --> 31:16.127
Water.

31:23.960 --> 31:24.961
Bridger, tell the others

31:25.080 --> 31:26.286
we'll camp here tonight.
(SPEAKING PAWNEE)

31:26.520 --> 31:28.727
I'm right here.

31:29.640 --> 31:32.883
I'll be right here...

31:33.440 --> 31:35.329
(MEN LAUGHING)

31:36.960 --> 31:38.485
(MEN SPEAKING FRENCH)

31:46.320 --> 31:47.924
Toussaint, he's here.

31:48.440 --> 31:51.046
I thought he wouldn't make it.

31:52.840 --> 31:55.764
I'm glad you made it here.

31:56.320 --> 31:59.130
We need horses and rifles.

31:59.760 --> 32:01.842
We bring you many pelts.

32:02.080 --> 32:06.483
No horses... just what we agreed.

32:07.320 --> 32:09.527
Take all the pelts you want.

32:09.920 --> 32:12.810
We need horses and rifles.

32:13.200 --> 32:16.124
I need a woman with big tits...

32:16.200 --> 32:17.884
Who can cook.

32:18.520 --> 32:20.841
We can't give you any horses.

32:22.040 --> 32:23.041
What's he saying?

32:23.042 --> 32:24.882
I don't know, something about horses.

32:24.883 --> 32:27.008
Bring us something to drink... some whisky.

32:28.440 --> 32:30.681
Tell him to stop asking about the horses.

32:33.000 --> 32:34.525
Always good doing business with you.

32:35.000 --> 32:36.365
Horses.

32:36.880 --> 32:38.041
No horses.

32:39.200 --> 32:40.929
All we can trade are guns and ammunition.

32:41.720 --> 32:45.441
Tell him if he asks about horses again,
there is no deal.

32:46.000 --> 32:49.243
Where did you get these? The Americans?

32:49.880 --> 32:51.405
They're already branded.

32:51.880 --> 32:55.726
I'll only be able to get
half price for them.

32:56.720 --> 32:58.768
Get him away from there.

32:58.880 --> 33:00.370
I said no horses.

33:01.080 --> 33:03.128
We'll take these three horses.

33:03.400 --> 33:04.970
I'm not going to say it again.

33:05.080 --> 33:06.682
They aren't part of the deal.

33:06.683 --> 33:08.364
Now tell your man to step away.

33:08.480 --> 33:11.290
We had an agreement, you have to honor it.

33:11.880 --> 33:17.091
<i>In French</i>
You stand there and talk to me about honor?

33:17.560 --> 33:20.404
I told you he speaks French.

33:21.920 --> 33:24.002
Those pelts are stolen.

33:28.040 --> 33:31.761
You all have stolen everything from us.

33:34.000 --> 33:35.650
Everything!

33:35.920 --> 33:37.365
The land.

33:37.760 --> 33:39.808
The animals.

33:40.400 --> 33:45.406
Two white men snuck into our village,
and took my daughter, Powaqa.

33:49.760 --> 33:54.766
We leave you these pelts
because honor demands it.

33:54.800 --> 33:57.999
I take your horses to find my daughter.

33:58.000 --> 34:01.800
You are free to try and stop me.

34:05.600 --> 34:09.002
Business is business.

34:11.480 --> 34:14.962
Prepare five horses for them.

34:20.880 --> 34:23.724
HENRY: I want everybody up
at the crack of dawn.

34:24.480 --> 34:26.562
Carrying Glass will be hard...

34:26.800 --> 34:29.724
so we need to get ahead
as far as possible.

34:30.719 --> 34:32.563
We'll divide into two groups.

34:33.080 --> 34:35.650
Fitzgerald, Jones, Fryman,

34:35.800 --> 34:38.087
you take the east side
of the river.

34:38.159 --> 34:40.561
Anderson, you scout up front.

34:40.679 --> 34:43.001
That claw
don't belong to you.

34:45.679 --> 34:47.170
It ain't for me.

35:04.760 --> 35:06.489
(WHEEZING)

35:09.400 --> 35:11.243
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

35:20.880 --> 35:22.564
(MEN ARGUING)

35:33.120 --> 35:34.565
Stop!

35:44.440 --> 35:46.090
(HAWK SPEAKING PAWNEE)

35:48.720 --> 35:50.131
(COUGHING)

36:01.800 --> 36:05.247
HENRY: Don't let him down!
Don't let him down!

36:16.800 --> 36:18.131
ANDERSON: Watch it.

36:18.720 --> 36:19.926
JONES: How we gonna
make it up this?

36:20.000 --> 36:21.126
FITZGERALD: Slow down.

36:21.240 --> 36:23.811
ANDERSON:
It's killing us, Captain!

36:24.360 --> 36:25.566
(ALL GRUNTING)

36:30.760 --> 36:32.603
HENRY: Lift it, Bridger!

36:33.440 --> 36:35.363
FITZGERALD: Goddamn it,
keep it steady.

36:35.440 --> 36:36.487
JIM: Lift it up higher.

36:36.560 --> 36:37.607
HAWK: I am.

36:39.440 --> 36:40.965
HENRY: And heave!

36:41.040 --> 36:42.201
(ALL GROAN)

36:42.280 --> 36:44.362
JONES: I'll go up and pull.

36:46.120 --> 36:47.281
(ALL GRUNTING)

36:48.280 --> 36:49.566
(ALL EXCLAIM)

36:50.880 --> 36:52.769
My foot!

36:52.840 --> 36:54.524
Enough of this shit!

36:54.640 --> 36:57.291
We'll never make it across
like this, Captain.

36:57.640 --> 36:59.324
He's burning up.
(COUGHING)

36:59.400 --> 37:00.606
(ALL PANTING)

37:01.200 --> 37:04.329
Cap'n, you ain't doing us
nor him no favors...

37:04.400 --> 37:06.846
by letting him
go on suffering like this.

37:08.480 --> 37:11.165
Captain, it's all
the same up here.

37:11.240 --> 37:14.722
We're gonna have to go back.
Find another way.

37:14.800 --> 37:16.404
(GLASS WHEEZING)

37:22.080 --> 37:24.401
Glass. Hugh.

37:25.560 --> 37:27.927
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

37:28.600 --> 37:30.921
Lay that rag over his eyes,
Mr. Bridger.

37:31.120 --> 37:32.201
HAWK: What?

37:32.280 --> 37:33.486
HENRY: Lay the rag
over his eyes.

37:33.560 --> 37:34.686
HAWK: Wait!

37:34.760 --> 37:35.921
HENRY: I'm sorry, Hugh.

37:36.000 --> 37:37.764
JIM: Sir, I can't do that.

37:37.840 --> 37:39.280
HAWK: How do we
get back without him?

37:39.360 --> 37:40.964
Only he knows the way.

37:41.040 --> 37:42.041
HENRY: Lay the rag
over his eyes.

37:42.120 --> 37:43.167
JIM: I can't.

37:43.280 --> 37:44.770
Wait! How do
we get back...

37:44.840 --> 37:46.330
(SPEAKING PAWNEE)

37:48.760 --> 37:50.603
HENRY: Lay it over his eyes!

37:51.120 --> 37:52.610
Step back.

37:54.760 --> 37:57.366
HAWK: Bridger, stop!
Bridger, Henry.

37:57.440 --> 37:59.283
Henry! Henry, please.

37:59.600 --> 38:02.285
Captain. Captain.
Please. Please leave...

38:02.640 --> 38:04.165
(HAWK SPEAKING PAWNEE)

38:04.880 --> 38:06.405
(GLASS CONTINUES WHEEZING)

38:12.440 --> 38:13.965
There's a $70 bonus

38:14.040 --> 38:16.884
from the Rocky Mountain Fur
Company to the two men...

38:16.960 --> 38:19.201
that stay with Glass
to see this through.

38:19.280 --> 38:20.406
HAWK: I'll stay!

38:20.480 --> 38:22.642
Me, too.
Money or not, I'll stay.

38:23.800 --> 38:25.325
I'll need a third.

38:25.640 --> 38:26.801
Sorry, Captain.

38:26.880 --> 38:30.168
I have a family.
I'm not crazy.

38:30.800 --> 38:33.724
Captain, three men
can't hold off a party of Ree,

38:33.800 --> 38:35.643
much less some boys.

38:36.000 --> 38:39.083
Besides, $70 ain't gonna buy
nobody a new set of ears.

38:39.160 --> 38:40.730
A hundred, then.

38:41.320 --> 38:43.561
This man is the only reason
we're still alive.

38:43.640 --> 38:45.927
We were 45 men
when this started.

38:46.000 --> 38:48.082
Now we're ten. Almost nine.

38:48.400 --> 38:50.323
HAWK: He's my father.
He can have my share.

38:50.400 --> 38:52.926
JIM: Mine, too.
He can have my share also.

38:57.680 --> 38:58.920
All right.

38:59.440 --> 39:01.204
If Mr. Bridger
feels the same way,

39:01.280 --> 39:02.611
I'll lag behind with them.

39:02.680 --> 39:03.920
You?
Yep.

39:04.000 --> 39:06.002
You already lost
my share of the pelts...

39:06.080 --> 39:07.889
so I got no choice
but to make it up

39:07.960 --> 39:09.530
by some other means.

39:09.840 --> 39:11.490
Sticking around
for another day or two

39:11.560 --> 39:13.130
don't make no difference.

39:13.200 --> 39:15.680
$300... at least I get to
go home with something.

39:15.760 --> 39:18.684
Glass is to be cared
for until, understood?

39:19.040 --> 39:21.691
Yeah. You have my word.
I understand.

39:23.280 --> 39:24.691
HENRY: You boys get him
down off this slope

39:24.760 --> 39:26.683
and somewhere safe
before dark.

39:27.040 --> 39:28.371
Fitzgerald.

39:30.840 --> 39:33.366
Glass is to be cared for
as long as necessary.

39:33.720 --> 39:35.643
And a proper burial
when it's time.

39:35.720 --> 39:36.881
He's earned it.

39:37.720 --> 39:39.131
I understand.

39:42.400 --> 39:43.890
You hurt yourself?

39:44.640 --> 39:46.051
ANDERSON: I'll be fine.

39:50.200 --> 39:51.850
(GLASS WHEEZING)

39:52.760 --> 39:54.125
(HAWK SPEAKING PAWNEE)

39:54.240 --> 39:56.971
Can you hear that wind, father?

39:59.880 --> 40:05.284
Remember what mother used to say
about the wind?

40:06.480 --> 40:11.805
The wind cannot defeat
a tree with strong roots.

40:17.440 --> 40:21.684
You are still breathing...

40:24.280 --> 40:28.729
I miss her so much.

40:34.000 --> 40:35.968
(SPEAKING PAWNEE)

40:45.600 --> 40:47.125
(GLASS SPEAKING PAWNEE)

40:49.200 --> 40:51.931
I will be right here...

40:53.360 --> 40:55.488
I'm right here.

40:59.880 --> 41:04.920
As long as you can still grab a breath,
you fight.

41:06.320 --> 41:08.800
<i>You breathe. Keep breathing.</i>

41:09.080 --> 41:10.280
(GLASS'S WIFE SPEAKING PAWNEE)

41:10.360 --> 41:13.842
<i>When there is a storm...</i>

41:15.600 --> 41:20.481
<i>And you stand in front of a tree...</i>

41:22.360 --> 41:23.600
(GUNSHOT)

41:25.520 --> 41:32.529
<i>If you look at its branches,
you swear it will fall.</i>

41:42.240 --> 41:50.240
<i>But if you watch the trunk,
you will see its stability.</i>

41:56.800 --> 41:58.165
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

42:08.400 --> 42:09.765
(FITZGERALD GRUNTING)

42:32.200 --> 42:33.725
FITZGERALD:
<i>Three hundred bucks</i>

42:33.800 --> 42:35.404
<i>goes a long way
toward retirement.</i>

42:35.720 --> 42:38.291
<i>Go down to Texas, find me
a decent piece of land,</i>

42:38.360 --> 42:40.249
<i>and start pissing in the wind.</i>

42:41.240 --> 42:44.403
Get me the hell out of this
godforsaken place.

42:44.480 --> 42:45.925
(JIM SCRAPING FLASK)

42:48.720 --> 42:50.404
Ree done that to you?

42:52.240 --> 42:53.651
I'm just asking.

42:54.640 --> 42:56.324
Yeah, they done it.

42:56.920 --> 42:59.491
They took their
sweet time with it.

43:00.560 --> 43:01.960
At the start,
I didn't feel nothing.

43:02.000 --> 43:03.764
I just heard the sound...

43:04.080 --> 43:07.243
of the knife scraping
against my skull and...

43:07.600 --> 43:08.965
them all laughing
and whooping

43:09.040 --> 43:11.088
and hollering and whatnot.

43:11.440 --> 43:12.930
Then the blood came.

43:13.240 --> 43:16.005
It was cold. It started
streaming down my face,

43:16.080 --> 43:17.605
in my eyes, and...

43:18.000 --> 43:19.604
breathing it in.

43:20.080 --> 43:21.764
Choking on it.

43:22.920 --> 43:24.922
That's when I felt it.

43:25.440 --> 43:27.602
Yeah, felt all of it.

43:28.280 --> 43:30.760
I got my head
turned inside out.

43:31.680 --> 43:32.886
JIM: Jesus.

43:32.960 --> 43:34.962
Them Indians
down Texas way...

43:35.280 --> 43:38.124
they may rob you,
but they ain't gonna take your topknot.

43:39.360 --> 43:40.885
JIM: When was it?

43:44.120 --> 43:45.610
Goddamn it,

43:45.680 --> 43:48.968
will you quit that noise now,
will you?

43:49.280 --> 43:50.486
Quit it.

44:16.000 --> 44:17.604
FITZGERALD:
<i>I'm falling further back</i>

44:17.680 --> 44:20.251
<i>from Henry and the boys
on account of tending to you.</i>

44:24.680 --> 44:25.920
Got to get up
the damn mountain,

44:26.000 --> 44:28.321
but winter
keeps chasing us down.

44:31.160 --> 44:34.528
If you ready
to take the sacrament...

44:35.680 --> 44:37.682
I can do that for you.

44:42.840 --> 44:44.922
What you holding to, Glass?

44:48.520 --> 44:49.681
You know...

44:50.440 --> 44:52.283
it would be better...

44:52.360 --> 44:55.569
if you were to take that
last breath of yours now...

44:55.640 --> 44:57.130
for all of us.

44:59.680 --> 45:01.523
Now you hung tough.

45:01.880 --> 45:03.450
And that's something.

45:04.520 --> 45:05.885
I'm begging you.

45:05.960 --> 45:08.167
Them Ree are so close
I can smell 'em.

45:08.240 --> 45:10.561
You can smell 'em, too.

45:10.640 --> 45:13.041
You got to think of your boy.
All right?

45:13.120 --> 45:14.724
'Cause you're gonna kill him.

45:15.040 --> 45:17.122
You'll kill us all.

45:17.200 --> 45:18.531
(MUTTERING)

45:24.120 --> 45:26.327
I can muzzle you
if you like.

45:26.400 --> 45:28.323
Take away this suffering
quick and easy.

45:28.400 --> 45:31.404
No one ever has to know
that you give up.

45:32.560 --> 45:35.643
All you have to do is blink
if you want me to do that.

45:36.560 --> 45:38.403
(GRUNTING SOFTLY)

45:41.920 --> 45:44.161
Save your boy and blink.

45:53.920 --> 45:56.241
You just have to blink.

46:01.240 --> 46:03.607
Yeah. There it is.

46:04.080 --> 46:05.525
You'd best hope
the good Lord'll

46:05.600 --> 46:07.602
get His ass here
quick, huh?

46:11.520 --> 46:13.841
Maybe He'll forgive your sins,
maybe not.

46:13.920 --> 46:16.048
Thus I do commend thee
to the Lord.

46:16.120 --> 46:17.531
(GLASS CHOKING)

46:17.600 --> 46:21.969
Through Jesus Christ the Lord
of all reality and mercy...

46:22.360 --> 46:25.728
and the Father
and the Creator, I hold thee...

46:25.800 --> 46:28.041
Get away! Get away!

46:28.120 --> 46:31.647
You okay?
Jim! Jim! Help!

46:42.760 --> 46:43.807
HAWK: Help!

46:43.880 --> 46:45.211
Calm down.

46:45.320 --> 46:47.129
Jim! Help!

46:47.240 --> 46:49.891
Don't shout! You're gonna
get us all killed!

46:49.960 --> 46:52.361
Keep away! I'll tell
the Captain what you did.

46:52.440 --> 46:53.965
They'll hang you!

46:54.080 --> 46:56.481
They'll hang you! Jim, help!

46:56.560 --> 46:58.642
We have an understanding.

47:02.240 --> 47:04.402
What's fucking wrong
with you people?

47:04.480 --> 47:05.686
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

47:15.000 --> 47:16.331
Shit.

47:17.680 --> 47:19.842
(GLASS CONTINUES MUFFLED SCREAMING)

47:30.440 --> 47:32.283
(CONTINUES MUFFLED SCREAMING)

48:17.240 --> 48:19.242
JIM: I got one beaver, Hawk.

48:21.080 --> 48:22.730
Breathing changed?

48:24.400 --> 48:26.243
I hadn't noticed.

48:27.560 --> 48:29.403
Damn, he's cold as ice.

48:31.080 --> 48:33.082
Here you go, Mr. Glass.

48:33.160 --> 48:35.925
This will help you.
Keep you warm.

48:36.920 --> 48:38.251
It's all right.

48:40.160 --> 48:41.605
Where's Hawk?

48:42.920 --> 48:44.524
He ain't with you?

48:45.760 --> 48:46.841
No.

48:46.920 --> 48:48.251
No?

48:48.360 --> 48:50.124
(GLASS SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

48:53.280 --> 48:55.362
I understand, Mr. Glass.

48:55.440 --> 48:58.444
It's all right.
I think I'll get a fire going.

48:58.760 --> 49:01.286
FITZGERALD: Yeah.
Sounds like a good idea.

49:02.240 --> 49:03.571
(SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

49:07.440 --> 49:08.771
JIM: Hawk!

49:12.120 --> 49:13.451
<i>Hawk!</i>

49:35.240 --> 49:36.730
FITZGERALD: Shh. Ree.

49:36.800 --> 49:39.724
There's about 20 of them
down by the creek.

49:39.800 --> 49:43.646
They're headed this way.
Grab your shit and let's go.

49:45.400 --> 49:47.926
Shit. What do we do?

49:48.000 --> 49:49.729
FITZGERALD: Run, right now.

49:49.840 --> 49:51.001
What about Hawk?

49:51.080 --> 49:53.003
He ain't our problem no more.

49:53.080 --> 49:54.491
We can't just leave him.

49:54.560 --> 49:56.244
Either he's gutted or scalped.

49:56.320 --> 49:58.766
And if he ain't
he can find us, can't he?

49:58.840 --> 50:00.683
What about Glass?

50:00.760 --> 50:03.127
He ain't our problem.
Like us, he's on his own.

50:03.200 --> 50:05.806
We made a promise
to the Captain.

50:05.880 --> 50:07.530
A proper burial
when the time was needed.

50:07.600 --> 50:09.523
He needs that rifle!

50:09.600 --> 50:13.924
He couldn't do nothing with it
if you tarred it to his hand.

50:14.000 --> 50:15.764
We can't do this.

50:15.840 --> 50:17.524
We got no fucking choice.

50:17.600 --> 50:19.523
JIM: No, we can't.
Look at him.

50:21.680 --> 50:24.047
All right, shit, then, buddy.
Get him up.

50:24.120 --> 50:25.451
You want to take him?

50:25.520 --> 50:27.284
(GLASS GROANING)

50:28.200 --> 50:29.690
Come on now!

50:29.880 --> 50:32.804
JIM: Easy. Slowly, Fitz.
Easy with him.

50:34.040 --> 50:35.121
(JIM GROANS)

50:35.200 --> 50:36.850
FITZGERALD:
Just get your shit.

50:36.920 --> 50:38.365
Get your shit!
(GLASS SCREAMING)

50:39.200 --> 50:40.531
Shut up.

50:44.360 --> 50:45.805
Shut up!

50:46.360 --> 50:47.566
JIM: Hold up!

50:49.040 --> 50:50.280
(GLASS GROANING)

50:50.400 --> 50:52.562
Fitz. What are you doing?

50:52.640 --> 50:54.369
What does it look like?

50:54.440 --> 50:56.727
Proper burial.
Like you wanted.

50:56.800 --> 50:58.643
JIM: No, not like this.

50:58.720 --> 50:59.881
FITZGERALD: Why not?

51:00.680 --> 51:03.411
He's alive, Fitz.
He's alive.

51:05.560 --> 51:06.891
So shoot him.

51:09.840 --> 51:11.285
(GLASS SHOUTING)

51:19.840 --> 51:21.842
I have to go.
I have to go.

51:22.920 --> 51:25.241
I'm sorry, Mr. Glass.
I'm sorry.

51:26.160 --> 51:28.000
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
(PROTESTING INDISTINCTLY)

51:30.360 --> 51:32.169
(WHEEZING)

51:34.720 --> 51:35.960
(JIM GROANS)

51:42.440 --> 51:44.602
MURPHY: Captain! This way!

51:45.600 --> 51:48.126
There's a path down here!

51:49.760 --> 51:51.603
ANDERSON:
There ain't shit down there!

51:51.680 --> 51:53.125
We got to climb over!

51:53.200 --> 51:54.645
JONES:
Glass said to stay east!

51:54.720 --> 51:57.121
ANDERSON:
Glass can go to hell!

51:57.960 --> 51:59.371
HENRY: What's the map say?

51:59.440 --> 52:01.807
Keep climbing.
We climb, Captain.

52:01.880 --> 52:03.530
We keep climbing.

52:03.640 --> 52:05.449
Till we reach Old Gabe.

52:09.640 --> 52:10.971
We climb.

52:12.280 --> 52:13.805
We got to wait for Murph.

52:14.120 --> 52:15.804
ANDERSON: Yeah.
You wait for him.

52:16.640 --> 52:17.971
Captain?

52:20.960 --> 52:22.246
Sir...

52:22.320 --> 52:24.687
Murphy says
there's a way down there.

52:24.760 --> 52:26.250
Who we following?

52:26.320 --> 52:27.810
ANDERSON:
You follow who you want!

52:27.880 --> 52:29.405
I'm going up!

52:30.480 --> 52:32.005
Stubby, keep going up!

52:32.080 --> 52:34.321
JONES: Murph! Come here!

52:53.840 --> 52:55.490
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

53:08.320 --> 53:10.084
(PANTING)

53:21.520 --> 53:22.931
(SCREAMS)

53:27.800 --> 53:29.802
(WHEEZING)

53:35.520 --> 53:36.965
(GRUNTING LOUDLY)

53:37.200 --> 53:38.929
(GASPING)

54:10.040 --> 54:11.690
(GRUNTING)

54:18.880 --> 54:20.803
(PANTING)

54:42.440 --> 54:43.726
(GRUNTING)

55:55.000 --> 55:56.240
(SPEAKING PAWNEE)

55:56.360 --> 56:00.410
I'm not leaving you, son.

56:02.360 --> 56:04.966
I'm right here.

57:10.920 --> 57:12.445
FITZGERALD: Fire's done.

57:13.280 --> 57:15.442
I can't even feel my feet.

57:17.600 --> 57:20.524
Didn't we put enough distance
between us and them Ree?

57:20.600 --> 57:23.649
A dozen Ree can make
twice as good time as we can.

57:23.720 --> 57:25.484
Twenty.
What?

57:27.600 --> 57:29.284
You said you saw
twenty Ree.

57:29.360 --> 57:31.601
Yeah? What you
talking about?

57:34.800 --> 57:36.370
You woke me up.
Mmm-hmm.

57:37.640 --> 57:39.881
You said you saw
twenty Ree by the creek.

57:39.960 --> 57:41.962
Well, yeah,
twenty, a dozen...

57:42.040 --> 57:43.121
it don't matter.

57:43.200 --> 57:46.807
I wasn't gonna hang around
counting fucking feathers.

57:49.800 --> 57:51.211
As a matter of fact...

57:52.960 --> 57:55.725
what was you doing down
by the creek all by yourself?

57:56.560 --> 57:58.767
I'd already brought up
plenty of water.

58:00.440 --> 58:01.726
Hey!

58:02.720 --> 58:05.246
Answer me, Fitzgerald.
I asked you a question.

58:06.560 --> 58:09.530
Don't question me
on account of you feel guilty.

58:09.600 --> 58:11.887
Answer me
or I'll blow your head off.

58:11.960 --> 58:14.122
You got
a short-term memory, boy.

58:14.600 --> 58:16.921
Your ass would be floating
around the Missouri right now

58:17.000 --> 58:18.650
if it wasn't for me.

58:20.640 --> 58:22.642
You want to ask questions?

58:22.760 --> 58:25.081
What you want to ask?
If you want to know, ask it.

58:25.280 --> 58:26.566
Hmm?

58:26.640 --> 58:27.971
You want to know
why you left.

58:28.080 --> 58:30.208
Mr. Glass back there
for dead, huh?

58:30.280 --> 58:33.568
Or why you left your little
boyfriend running around?

58:33.640 --> 58:36.484
You want to know
if he's still alive?

58:36.840 --> 58:39.002
I'll tell you why.
It's 'cause you ain't a man yet.

58:39.360 --> 58:41.328
It's 'cause you was
scared shitless.

58:41.400 --> 58:42.845
You're scared now.

58:42.920 --> 58:44.285
The Ree.

58:44.360 --> 58:45.691
What of them?

58:46.520 --> 58:48.443
Tell me, did you see 'em?

58:48.520 --> 58:50.682
Put your rifle down.
Did you see the Ree?

58:52.880 --> 58:54.120
No.

58:55.360 --> 58:57.203
Not a single one.

58:59.800 --> 59:03.361
You fucking lied to me?
You lied to me!

59:03.440 --> 59:04.805
(COUGHS)

59:05.120 --> 59:06.485
(GASPS)

59:07.120 --> 59:09.726
I had to scare
some sense into you, boy.

59:10.040 --> 59:12.202
Glass was dead.
Hawk we don't know about.

59:12.560 --> 59:15.211
No point in either of us
dying either, you understand?

59:15.560 --> 59:17.688
The way I see it,
I saved your life twice now.

59:17.760 --> 59:19.888
I ought to be God to you.

59:20.560 --> 59:23.723
And God giveth...
and God taketh away.

59:26.880 --> 59:28.405
(GUN CLICKS)
(GASPS)

59:31.160 --> 59:32.525
Lucky fucker.

59:33.920 --> 59:37.208
Next time you want to
shoot somebody...

59:37.280 --> 59:39.123
you might
want to use powder,

59:39.200 --> 59:40.770
prime your rifle.

59:43.760 --> 59:47.401
Come on. Let's git.
Grab your shit.

59:48.760 --> 59:50.091
(SNIFFLES)

01:01:22.360 --> 01:01:23.691
(GRUNTS)

01:02:12.280 --> 01:02:14.408
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:02:53.800 --> 01:02:55.802
(GLASS GRUNTING)

01:03:44.880 --> 01:03:46.245
(SNIFFS)

01:03:47.080 --> 01:03:48.411
(SPEAKING ARIKARA)

01:03:48.560 --> 01:03:52.690
Fresh blood. This could be Powaqa.

01:04:04.440 --> 01:04:05.726
A dead boy.

01:04:14.640 --> 01:04:16.449
A Pawnee boy.

01:04:16.680 --> 01:04:18.205
Let's go.

01:04:22.600 --> 01:04:24.090
(GRUNTING)

01:05:01.240 --> 01:05:03.083
(PANTING)

01:05:28.720 --> 01:05:30.563
(COUGHING)

01:06:45.040 --> 01:06:46.644
(COUGHS)

01:07:08.600 --> 01:07:11.410
(SCREAMING)

01:07:29.640 --> 01:07:31.165
(ALL PANTING)

01:08:10.760 --> 01:08:12.285
(GLASS SNORING)

01:08:20.520 --> 01:08:21.965
(GRUNTING)

01:08:34.319 --> 01:08:35.526
